t%20by%20the%20movement%20of%20major%20tech%20companies%2C%20including%20Apple%2C%20Amazon%2C%20and%20Tesla%2C%20into%20the%20city.%20Median%20home%20prices%20in%20Austin%20more%20than%20doubled%20between%202011%20and%202021%20as%20the%20city's%20median%20household%20income%20rose%20from%20%2455%2C744%20to%20%2480%2C954%20in%20roughly%20the%20same%20time%20period%2C%20the%20Austin%20Chamber%20of%20Commerce%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECity%20lawmakers%20are%20finally%20finding%20some%20success%20in%20their%20efforts%20to%20boost%20housing%20affordability.%20The%20city%20council%20on%20Thursday%20approved%20a%20resolution%20that%20would%20reduce%20the%20minimum%20lot%20size%20for%20a%20home%20by%20more%20than%20half%20and%20allow%20up%20to%20three%20units%20on%20each%20residential%20lot.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fservices.austintexas.gov%2Fedims%2Fdocument.cfm%3Fid%3D412080%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eupzoning%20measures%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20supported%20by%20nine%20of%20the%20council's%2011%20members%2C%20are%20designed%20to%20promote%20the%20construction%20of%20so-called%20%26quot%3Bgentle%20density%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20also%20known%20as%20infill%20housing%20or%20missing-middle%20housing.%20It%20would%20allow%20townhomes%2C%20duplexes%2C%20and%20triplexes%20to%20be%20built%20on%20lots%20that%20only%20single-family%20detached%20homes%20could%20previously%20sit%20on.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20resolution%20also%20asks%20the%20city%20manager%20to%20review%20regulations%20on%20how%20tall%20homes%20can%20be%2C%20how%20far%20they%20need%20to%20be%20from%20the%20street%2C%20and%20how%20much%20of%20a%20lot%20can%20be%20covered%20by%20surfaces%20like%20rooftops%20and%20driveways%20that%20don't%20absorb%20rainfall.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAustin%20also%20recently%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kut.org%2Fbusiness%2F2023-05-04%2Faustin-slams-the-brakes-on-parking-mandates%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eended%20its%20mandates%3C%2Fa%3E%20requiring%20a%20certain%20amount%20of%20parking%20spots%20be%20built%20with%20every%20new%20home%20%E2%80%94%20a%20move%20that%20is%20also%20expected%20to%20reduce%20housing%20costs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20city%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkinder.rice.edu%2Furbanedge%2Fdespite-pandemic-austin-dallas-and-houston-all-built-more-housing-last-year-it-still%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20built%20new%20housing%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20a%20faster%20rate%20than%20most%20US%20cities%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20its%20restrictive%20zoning%20policies%20simply%20haven't%20allowed%20it%20to%20build%20as%20much%20as%20it%20needs.%20The%20Texas%20capital's%201980s%20land%20development%20code%20makes%20it%20illegal%20to%20build%20anything%20other%20one%20single-family%20home%20on%20a%20lot%20that's%20at%20least%205%2C750%20square%20feet%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-is-austin-so-expensive-map-housing-market-single-family-2021-11%5C%22%3Ein%20most%20of%20the%20city.%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpponents%20of%20the%20rezoning%20efforts%20say%20more%20dense%20new%20housing%20would%20change%20the%20character%20of%20their%20neighborhoods%2C%20increase%20congestion%2C%20and%20displace%20longtime%20residents%2C%20among%20other%20concerns.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearch%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffurmancenter.org%2Fresearch%2Fpublication%2Fsupply-skepticismnbsp-housing-supply-and-affordability%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20found%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20increasing%20the%20market-rate%20housing%20supply%20makes%20housing%20more%20affordable%20for%20both%20middle-%20and%20low-income%20residents%2C%20despite%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theatlantic.com%2Fideas%2Farchive%2F2022%2F11%2Fus-housing-supply-shortage-crisis-2022%2F672240%2F%5C%22%20tar