0are%20split%20on%20the%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20crackdown%20has%20been%20in%20the%20works%20for%20two%20years%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20enforcement%20is%20a%20result%20of%20a%202021%20law%20that%20expanded%20short-term%20rental%20licensing%20requirements.%20Previously%2C%20only%20spots%20that%20rented%20out%20for%20more%20than%2090%20days%20a%20year%20were%20required%20to%20be%20licensed%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwhyy.org%2Farticles%2Fphilly-council-passes-tougher-airbnb-regulations%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20Philadelphia%20news%20station%20WHYY%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPhiladelphia%20will%20begin%20dual%20outreach%2C%20first%20to%20Airbnb%20and%20Vrbo%20to%20take%20down%20illegal%20listings%2C%20and%20then%20to%20hosts%20themselves%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.phila.gov%2F2023-07-13-unlicensed-short-term-rental-properties-delisting-process-begins%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DUpon%2520review%2520L%2526I%2520has%2520determined%2Cproperties%2520today%2520July%252012%252C%25202023.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20city's%20Department%20of%20Licenses%20and%20Inspections.%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECouncilmember%20Mark%20Squilla%2C%20who%20introduced%20the%20measure%2C%20told%20WHYY%20in%202021%20that%20%26quot%3Bby%20doing%20this%20we%20will%20have%20more%20control%20over%20the%20bad%20operators.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAirbnb%2C%20for%20its%20part%2C%20says%20it's%20working%20with%20the%20city.%20%26quot%3BFor%20months%20Airbnb%20has%20worked%20closely%20with%20the%20City%20of%20Philadelphia%20to%20ensure%20they%20have%20the%20necessary%20tools%20and%20support%20to%20effectively%20enforce%20their%20current%20rules%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20Airbnb%20spokesperson%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20also%20developed%20and%20distributed%20materials%20and%20messaging%20to%20our%20Hosts%2