e%20quickly%20with%20the%20relief%2C%20as%20the%20law%20said%20the%20education%20secretary%20could%20waive%20or%20modify%20student%20loans%20in%20connection%20with%20a%20national%20emergency.%20While%20the%20high%20court%20ruled%20that%20Biden%20overreached%20in%20his%20authority%20by%20using%20that%20law%20for%20broad%20student-debt%20relief%2C%20it%20did%20not%20rule%20out%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-struck-down-will-biden-try-again-relief-2023-6%5C%22%3Ethe%20Higher%20Education%20Act%20as%20an%20alternative%20route%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20get%20debt%20cancellation%20to%20borrowers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20law%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-struck-down-will-biden-try-again-relief-2023-6%5C%22%3Esays%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Education%20Department%20can%20%26quot%3Benforce%2C%20pay%2C%20compromise%2C%20waive%2C%20or%20release%20any%20right%2C%20title%2C%20claim%2C%20lien%2C%20or%20demand%26quot%3B%20related%20to%20federal%20student%20debt.%20But%20that%20law%20requires%20Biden%20to%20go%20through%20the%20negotiated-rulemaking%20process.%20Before%20the%20department%20implements%20a%20policy%2C%20it%20has%20to%20post%20its%20proposal%20on%20the%20Federal%20Register%20to%20allow%20the%20public%20to%20comment%20on%20it.%20That%20initial%20proposal%20is%20known%20as%20a%20Notice%20of%20Proposed%20Rulemaking.%20Once%20the%20department%20publishes%20its%20proposal%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-biden-new-plan-student-loan-debt-forgiveness-hearing-2023-7%5C%22%3Eit%20holds%20a%20public%20hearing%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20it%20and%20then%20undergoes%20a%20series%20of%20negotiations%20with%20stakeholders%20and%20experts%20until%20all%20parties%20reach%20a%20consensus%20on%20the%20regulation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20process%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-long-will-take-cancel-student-debt-higher-education-act-2023-7%5C%22%3Ehistorically%20taken%20a%20long%20time%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20meaning%20that%20the%20new%20attempt%20at%20broad%20student-debt%20relief%20may%20not%20arrive%20for%20a%20while.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20set%20timeline%20for%20the%20department%20to%20complete%20this%20process%2C%20and%20it%20has%20varied%20in%20the%20past.%20But%20under%20the%20Biden%20administration%2C%20the%20fastest%20negotiated-rulemaking%20process%20for%20a%20series%20of%20higher-education%20reforms%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.federalregister.gov%2Fdocuments%2F2021%2F08%2F10%2F2021-16953%2Fnegotiated-rulemaking-committee-negotiator-nominations-and-schedule-of-committee-meetings%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estarted%20in%20August%202021%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20official%20rule%20was%20published%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.federalregister.gov%2Fdocuments%2F2022%2F11%2F01%2F2022-23447%2Finstitutional-eligibility-under-the-higher-education-act-of-1965-as-amended-student-assistance%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eat%20the%20beginning%20of%20November%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20totaling%20about%2015%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20the%20timeline%20for%20this%20new%20plan%20for%20student-debt%20relief%20could%20be%20quicker%2C%20and%20Education%20Department%20officials%20have%20said%20they%20will%20work%20as%20fast%20as%20they%20can%20under%20the%20process%20to%20get%20relief%20to%20borrowers.%20The%20timeline%20also%20does%20not%20account%20for%20any%20litigation%20that%20could%20arise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20want%20to%20help%20borrowers%20who%20were%20let%20down%20by%20the%20fundamental%20bargain%20of%20federal%20student%20loans%20%E2%80%94%20that%20investments%20in%20yourself%20and%20your%20education%20will%20help%20lead%20you%20to%20a%20better%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20Under%20Secretary%20of%20Education%20James%20Kvaal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-biden-new-plan-student-loan-debt-forgiveness-hearing-2023-7%5C%22%3Esaid%20during%20a%20Tuesday%20public%20hearing%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BBy%20those%20who%20have%20seen%20their%20debts%20get%20out%20of%20hand%2C%20even%20as%20they%20make%20the%20payments%20we%20ask%20of%20them%2C%20we%20will%20help%20as%20many%20borrowers%20as%20possible%2C%20and%20we%20will%20work%20as%20quickly%20as%20possible%20under%20the%20law.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20comes%20next%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20department%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-biden-new-plan-student-loan-debt-forgiveness-hearing-2023-7%5C%22%3Eheld%20the%20public%20hearing%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Biden's%20new%20debt%20relief%20plan%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20during%20which%20department%20officials%20heard%20from%20borrowers%2C%20advocates%2C%20and%20experts%20on%20how%20they%20thought%20the%20proposal%20should%20be%20shaped.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20now%20in%20the%20process%20of%20selecting%20negotiators.%20Negotiators%20are%20nominated%20by%20the%20public%20and%20selected%20by%20the%20department%2C%20which%20will%20solicit%20nominations%20via%20the%20Federal%20Register.%20According%20to%20the%20website%2C%20negotiators%20could%20include%20%26quot%3Bstudents%2C%20legal%20assistance%20organizations%20that%20represent%20students%2C%20institutions%20of%20higher%20education%2C%20state%20student%20grant%20agencies%2C%20guaranty%20agencies%2C%20lenders%2C%20secondary%20markets%2C%20loan%20servicers%2C%20guaranty%20agency%20servicers%2C%20collection%20agencies%2C%20state%20agencies%2C%20and%20accrediting%20agencies.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20negotiating%20committees%20are%20formed%2C%20they%20will%20meet%20for%20three%20sessions%20at%20monthly%20intervals%2C%20and%20each%20session%20usually%20lasts%20three%20days%2C%20but%20the%20number%20of%20sessions%20could%20change%20depending%20on%20how%20the%20negotiations%20play%20out.%20For%20negotiators%20to%20reach%20a%20consensus%20on%20t