ugs%20dumped%20off%20the%20coast%20of%20Florida%2C%20sending%20them%20a%20little%20crazy%2C%20scientists%20say%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224256%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20bull%20shark%20comes%20close%20to%20inspect%20a%20tourist's%20camera%20during%20an%20eco%20tourism%20shark%20dive%20off%20in%20Florida%20on%20May%205%2C%202022.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F649a5e14867d960019d925dd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222832%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20bull%20shark%20comes%20close%20to%20inspect%20a%20tourist's%20camera%20during%20an%20eco%20tourism%20shark%20dive%20off%20in%20Florida%20on%20May%205%2C%202022.%3Cp%3EJoseph%20Prezioso%2FAnadolu%20Agency%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ESharks%20might%20be%20consuming%20drugs%20that%20are%20dumped%20off%20the%20Florida%20coast%2C%20scientists%20say.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAn%20upcoming%20Shark%20Week%20episode%20will%20investigate%20whether%20the%20drugs%20are%20impacting%20the%20animals.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20scientists%20observed%20unusual%20behavior%20from%20some%20sharks%2C%20including%20one%20fixating%20on%20an%20imaginary%20object.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20think%20hungry%20sharks%20might%20be%20feeding%20on%20drugs%20dumped%20off%20the%20Florida%20coast%20and%20sending%20them%20a%20little%20crazy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20upcoming%20Discovery%20Channel%20Shark%20Week%20episode%2C%20%26quot%3BCocaine%20Sharks%2C%26quot%3B%20looks%20into%20the%20theory%2C%20with%20its%20title%20referencing%20the%20%26quot%3BCocaine%20Bear%26quot%3B%20that%20ingested%20nearly%2075%20lb%20of%20cocaine%20in%201985%20%E2%80%93%20and%20loosely%20inspired%20a%20comedy%20horror%20film%20that%20came%20out%20earlier%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20catchy%20headline%20to%20shed%20light%20on%20a%20real%20problem%2C%20that%20everything%20we%20use%2C%20everything%20we%20manufacture%2C%20everything%20we%20put%20into%20our%20bodies%2C%20ends%20up%20in%20our%20wastewater%20streams%20and%20natural%20water%20bodies%2C%20and%20these%20aquatic%20life%20we%20depend%20on%20to%20survive%20are%20then%20exposed%20to%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dr.%20Tracy%20Fanara%2C%20a%20Florida-based%20environmental%20engineer%20and%20lead%20member%20of%20the%20research%20team%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fus-news%2F2023%2Fjul%2F22%2Fcocaine-sharks-drugs-florida-coast%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Guardian.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStudies%20had%20shown%20pharmaceuticals%2C%20including%20cocaine%2C%20methamphetamines%2C%20and%20ketamine%2C%20had%20affected%20fish%2C%20Fanara%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHuge%20bales%20of%20cocaine%20have%20washed%20up%20on%20Florida's%20beaches%20for%20decades%2C%20usually%20being%20thrown%20into%20the%20sea%20by%20traffickers%20fleeing%20from%20law%20enforcement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Coast%20Guard%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.news.uscg.mil%2FPress-Releases%2Farticle%2F3431687%2Fcoast-guard-offloads-more-than-186-million-in-illegal-narcotics%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20it%20had%20recovered%20more%20than%20%24186m%20of%20illegal%20narcotics%20seized%20in%20the%20Caribbean%20Sea%20and%20the%20Atlantic%20Ocean%20last%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20these%20cocaine%20bales%20are%20a%20point%20source%20of%20pollution%2C%20it's%20%26quot%3Bvery%20plausible%26quot%3B%20sharks%20can%20be%20affected%20by%20this%20chemical%2C%20Fanara%20said.%20%26quot%3BCocaine%20is%20so%20soluble%20that%20any%20of%20those%20packages%20open%20just%20a%20little%2C%20the%20structural%20integrity%20is%20destroyed%2C%20and%20the%20drug%20is%20in%20the%20water.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20upcoming%20Shark%20Week%20episode%2C%20Fanara%20and%20British%20marine%20biologist%20Tom%20Hird%20conduct%20a%20series%20of%20experiments%20to%20determine%20whether%20the%20sharks%20in%20waters%20around%20Florida%20were%20consuming%20the%20dumped%20narcotics%20and%20whether%20this%20affected%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20scientists%20observed%20unusual%20behavior%20by%20some%20of%20the%20sharks%2C%20per%20The%20Guardian.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20included%20a%20hammerhead%20swimming%20directly%20towards%20them%20while%20moving%20erratically%2C%20despite%20being%20a%20species%20that%20would%20typically%20avoid%20humans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20at%20one%20point%2C%20a%20sandbar%20shark%20was%20seen%20swimming%20in%20circles%20as%20it%20appeared%20to%20focus%20on%20an%20imaginary%20object%2C%20despite%20nothing%20being%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20scientists%20created%20packages%20that%20resembled%20cocaine%20bales%20and%20dropped%20them%20into%20the%20water%20to%20see%20how%20the%20sharks%20would%20respond.%20The%20sharks%20swam%20straight%20to%20the%20bales%20and%20took%20bites%20out%20of%20them%2C%20the%20outlet%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20also%20filled%20balls%20of%20bait%20with%20highly%20concentrated%20fish%20powder%20to%20simulate%20cocaine%20and%20see%20how%20the%20animals%20would%20react.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20set%20their%20brains%20aflame.%20It%20was%20crazy%2C%26quot%3B%20Hird%20says%20on%20the%20show%2C%20per%20The%20Guardian.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20said%20the%20reaction%20was%20similar%20to%20catnip%20on%20felines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20observations%20do%20not%20necessarily%20confirm%20that%20the%20sharks%20consume%20drugs%2C%20and%20Hind%20told%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livescience.com%2Fanimals%2Fsharks%2Fcocaine-sharks-off-florida-may-be-feasting-on-dumped-bales-of-drugs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELiveScience%3C%2Fa%3E%20he%20hopes%20the%20show%20will%20lead%20to%20more%20research%20in%20the%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca