o%20grow%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20having%20grown%20up%20online%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-hates-remote-work-office-jobs-work-from-home-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EGen%20Zers%20dislike%20working%20from%20home%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20more%20than%20other%20generations.%20Among%20Gen%20Z%2C%2057%25%20want%20in-person%20jobs%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.joblist.com%2Fjobs-reports%2F2023-trends-united-states-job-market-report%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20an%20online%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20about%203%2C100%C2%A0US%C2%A0job%20seekers%20conducted%20by%20Jobslist%20in%20the%20final%20months%20of%202022.%20The%20same%20survey%20found%20only%20one%20in%20three%20millennial%20and%20Gen%20X%20workers%20prefer%20IRL.%20For%20boomers%2C%20it%20was%2037%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Gen%20Z%20sentiment%20checks%20out%20for%20Farber.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20things%20like%20Slack%2C%20but%20I%20believe%20there's%20an%20overabundance%20of%20softwares%20trying%20to%20make%20it%20easier%20to%20work%20from%20home%2C%26quot%3B%20Farber%2C%20who%20worked%20in%20the%20JPMorgan%20office%20during%20an%20internship%20last%20summer%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can't%20replace%20being%20in%20the%20office%20and%20that%20comradery.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Farber's%20case%2C%20he%20should%20have%20plenty%20of%20company%20at%20the%20office.%20JPMorgan%2C%20like%20other%20large%20financial%20firms%2C%20is%20requiring%20many%20workers%20to%20be%20in%20the%20office%20most%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZehra%20Naqvi%2C%20a%2024-year-old%20at%20a%20financial-services%20company%2C%20said%20she%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-who-works-in-office-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eworks%20from%20her%20office%20every%20day%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20she%20gets%20her%20questions%20answered%20quickly%20and%20because%20she%20gets%20a%20fast%20read%20on%20how%20she's%20doing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHaving%20people%20on%20my%20team%20who%20had%20been%20doing%20the%20job%20for%20a%20year%20give%20me%20feedback%20on%20how%20I%20talked%20to%20a%20founder%20or%20how%20I%20explained%20something%20%E2%80%94%20that%20really%20helped%20my%20growth%2C%26quot%3B%20Naqvi%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe's%20also%20grown%20more%20confident%20in%20presenting%20herself%2C%20which%20is%20crucial%20for%20her%20career%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBeing%20in%20the%20office%20was%20really%20helpful%20for%20me%20to%20find%20my%20footing%20and%20lean%20into%20becoming%20the%20leader%20that%20I%20am%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Naqvi%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20a%20degree%2C%20you%20are%20performing%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20being%20in%20the%20office%20helps%20her%20be%20more%20aware%20of%20how%20she%20comes%20across%20to%20other%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWithout%20mentors%2C%20the%20office%20space%20loses%20purpose%20for%20Gen%20Z%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20of%20what%20Naqvi%20learned%2C%20and%20what%20Farber%20hopes%20to%20learn%2C%20comes%20from%20watching%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDavina%20Ramkissoon%2C%20a%20workplace%20psychologist%20in%20Dublin%2C%20said%20some%20fresh-faced%20workers%20worried%20they%20wouldn't%20get%20the%20development%20opportunities%20they%20wanted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSometimes%20you%20just%20learn%20via%20osmosis%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20seeing%20different%20experiences%20happen%20in%20real%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-remote-work-stunts-gen-z-career-growth-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EJoshua%20Roizman%2