0an%20astoundingly%20good%20Cillian%20Murphy%20%E2%80%93%20stares%20at%20ripples%20in%20a%20puddle.%20The%20%E2%80%98father%20of%20the%20atomic%20bomb%E2%80%99%20is%20probably%20thinking%20about%20legacy.%20And%20yet%2C%20nothing%20quite%20prepares%20us%20for%20a%20scene%20when%20an%20unclothed%20Oppenheimer%20is%20slinkily%20seated%20on%20a%20sofa%20with%20his%20legs%20crossed%2C%20across%20from%20his%20lover%20Jean%20(Florence%20Pugh)%20in%20a%20hotel%20room.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20a%20flashback%20linked%20to%20a%20hearing%2C%20where%20the%20pioneer%20scientist%20is%20being%20grilled%20about%20his%20past%20%E2%80%98transgressions%E2%80%99%20while%20being%20vetted%20for%20security%20clearance.%20Oppenheimer%20was%20married%20to%20Kitty%20(Emily%20Blunt)%20at%20the%20time%2C%20and%20Jean%20was%20known%20to%20be%20a%20card-carrying%20communist%2C%20especially%20on%20the%20brink%20of%20the%20Cold%20War.%20The%20hearing%20seems%20determined%20to%20discredit%20the%20man%20behind%20the%20Manhattan%20Project.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeated%20at%20the%20hearing%20wearing%20a%20crisp%20suit%2C%20the%20camera%20slowly%20pans%20from%20behind%20a%20character%20and%20we%20see%20stark-naked%20Oppenheimer%20in%20front%20of%20the%20committee.%20We%20soon%20realise%20we%E2%80%99re%20watching%20the%20scene%20from%20Kitty%E2%80%99s%20point-of-view%2C%20who%20is%20seeing%20her%20husband%20stripped%20of%20all%20dignity.%20She%20imagines%20Jean%20seated%20on%20his%20lap%2C%20staring%20directly%20at%20her.%20It%E2%80%99s%20an%20ingenious%20and%20confident%20swing%20by%20a%20director%20who%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20filmed%20a%20sex%20scene%20or%20nudity%20in%20nearly%20two%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENolan%20%E2%80%93%20one%20of%20the%20most%20hotly-debated%20filmmakers%20among%20cinephiles%20%E2%80%93%20revered%20for%20his%20big%20canvas%20ideas%20and%2C%20simultaneously%20reviled%20for%20writing%20himself%20into%20corners%2C%20is%20on%20solid%20ground%20in%20the%20biopic%20of%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20figures%20of%20the%2020th%20century.%20Adapted%20from%20Kai%20Bird%20and%20Martin%20J%20Sherwin%E2%80%99s%20Pulitzer-winner%2C%20%3Cem%3EAmerican%20Prometheus%3A%20The%20Triumph%20%26amp%3B%20Tragedy%20of%20J.%20Robert%20Oppenheimer%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%93%20this%20is%20arguably%20Nolan%20at%20his%20most%20socially%20conscious.%20Like%20most%20of%20his%20heroes%2C%20obsessive%20men%20each%20of%20them%2C%20Nolan%20mines%20Oppenheimer%20for%20a%20haunted%20guy%2C%20long%20before%20he%20manifested%20the%20power%20for%20humans%20to%20become%20destroyers%20of%20the%20world.%20When%20he%E2%80%99s%20asked%20about%20his%20time%20studying%20amongst%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20greatest%20scientific%20minds%20in%20Europe%2C%20he%20testifies%20to%20being%20homesick%2C%20terrible%20in%20the%20laboratory%2C%20and%20unable%20to%20sleep%20because%20of%20visions%20of%20%E2%80%98another%20world%E2%80%99.%20Nolan%E2%80%99s%20filmmaking%20is%20dynamic%20in%20this%20part%20%E2%80%93%20filling%20the%20screen%20with%20wondrous%20images.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FuYPbbksJxIg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20tells%20the%20story%20of%20Oppenheimer%20primarily%20through%20two%20sets%20of%20hearings%20%E2%80%93%20one%20where%20the%20scientist%20is%20asked%20about%20his%20alleged%20links%20to%20the%20Communist%20party%2C%20while%20his%20colleagues%20and%20friends%20are%20being%20made%20to%20testify%20about%20patriotism%20for%20America.%20Another%20is%20a%20congressional%20hearing%20of%20Lewis%20Strauss%20(Robert%20Downey%20Jr.)%20being%20vetted%20for%20a%20Cabinet%20position%20and%20asked%20about%20his%20dynamic%20with%20Oppenheimer%20over%20the%20years.%20Nolan%20differentiates%20the%20two%20timelines%20by%20showing%20Oppenheimer%E2%80%99s%20hearing%20and%20flashbacks%20in%20radiant%20colour%2C%20while%20Strauss%E2%80%99%20flashbacks%20and%20hearing%20appear%20in%20sharp%20black-and-white.%20It%E2%80%99s%20an%20efficient%20way%20to%20distinguish%2C%20prompting%20a%20rhythm%20for%20the%20visuals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EOppenheimer%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20a%20busy%20film%20with%20familiar%20faces%20in%20abundance.%20Downey%20Jr%2C%20who%20spent%20the%20better%20part%20of%20the%20last%20decade%20playing%20the%20smartest%20man%20in%20most%20films%2C%20plays%20a%20slimy%20politician%20with%20a%20chip%20on%20his%20shoulder.%20Matt%20Damon%2C%20who%20had%20a%20sensational%20special%20appearance%20in%20%3Cem%3EInterstellar%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2014)%2C%20gets%20a%20sizable%20role%20in%20this%20one%20as%20Lt.%20General%20Groves%20%E2%80%93%20who%20recruits%20Oppenheimer%20to%20be%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Manhattan%20project.%20Damon%E2%80%99s%20portly%20physique%20and%20self-assured%20tone%20is%20nicely%20at%20odds%20with%20Cillian%20Murphy%E2%80%99s%20frail%20build%2C%20but%20high-powered%20rebuttals.%20As%20Jean%2C%20Florence%20Pugh%20burns%20bright%20like%20a%20shooting%20star%2C%20for%20the%20few%20minutes%20she%20is%20on%20screen.%20Emily%20Blunt%20as%20Kitty%20is%20ferociously%20no-nonsense%2C%20which%20reminded%20me%20of%20Claire%20Foy%E2%80%99s%20turn%20as%20Janet%20Armstrong%20in%20%3Cem%3EFirst%20Man%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2018).%20Casey%20Affleck%20is%20chilling%20in%20a%20cameo%20as%20Boris%20Pash%20%E2%80%93%20in-charge%20of%20security%20of%20the%20Manhattan%20project%20%E2%80%93%20sneaking%20up%20on%20his%20subjects%20with%20his%20boyish%2C%20unassuming%20manner%2C%20before%20quietly%20trapping%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20film%2C%20however%2C%20belongs%20to%20Cillian%20Murphy%20showcasing%20the%20many%20sides%20to%20Oppenheimer%E2%80%99s%20personality.%20A%20brilliant%20scientist%2C%20he%E2%80%99s%20also%20equally%20immersed%20in%20social%20justice.%20We%E2%80%99re%20told%20he%20contributes%20a%20portion%20of%20his%20paycheck%20to%20help%20German%20colleagues%20escape%20the%20Nazi%20regime.%20He%E2%80%99s%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmayor%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Csheriff%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20town%20built%20around%20the%20Los%20Alamos%20laboratory%20in%20New%20Mexico%20but%20sobs%20like%20a%20teenager%20after%20being%20delivered%20bad%20news%20about%20a%20loved%20one.%20He%E2%80%99s%20curious%20and%20ambitious%20about%20accomplishing%20something%20dangerous%20%E2%80%93%20because%20he%20says%20it%E2%80%99s%20better%20he%20discovers%20it%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20fascists%20in%20Germany%20or%20Russia.%20However%2C%20he%E2%80%99s%20also%20equally%20torn%20about%20where%20this%20game%20of%20one-upmanship%20stops.%20A%20colleague%20accuses%20him%20of%20having%20become%20a%20%E2%80%98politician%2C%20who%20has%20left%20science%20far%20behind%E2%80%99%2C%20while%20trying%20to%20convince%20him%20to%20be%20their%20voice%20in%20the%20ears%20of%20the%20bigwig%20politicians%20in%20D.C%2C%20who%20haven%E2%80%99t%20fully%20grasped%20the%20direction%20they%E2%80%99re%20taking%20the%20world%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20much%20as%20%3Cem%3EOppenheimer%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20a%20showcase%20for%20its%20lead%20actor%20and%20director%2C%20the%20film%20also%20benefits%20tremendously%20from%20Ludwig%20Gorranson%E2%80%99s%20terrific%20score%20and%20Richard%20King%E2%80%99s%20excellent%20sound%20design.%20Especially%2C%20in%20three%20of%20the%20biggest%20scenes%20that%20Nolan%20sets%20up%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Trinity%20tests%2C%20the%20scene%20in%20which%20Kitty%20is%20summoned%20to%20testify%20about%20her%20husband%E2%80%99s%20character%2C%20and%20the%20%E2%80%98victory%E2%80%99%20speech%20that%20Oppenheimer%20has%20to%20find%20his%20way%20through%20after%20the%20bombings%20of%20Hiroshima%20and%20Nagasaki%20are%20announced%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98success%E2%80%99.%20Gorranson%E2%80%99s%20score%20is%20equal%20parts%20delicate%20and%20muscular%2C%20creeping%20up%20on%20the%20visuals%20or%20otherwise%20enhancing%20them%20in%20every%20which%20way.%20King%E2%80%99s%20impeccably%20designed%20silence%20fills%20up%20our%20senses%20about%20the%20magnitude%20of%20the%20Trinity%20test%2C%20without%20having%20us%20hear%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20probably%20for%20the%20best%20that%20Nolan%20fell%20out%20with%20long-time%20producers%2C%20Warner%20Bros%2C%20after%20the%20botched-up%20experience%20of%20releasing%20%3Cem%3ETenet%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2020)%20in%20theatres.%20It%20obviously%20resulted%20in%20every%20major%20studio%20and%20streaming%20service%20lining%20up%20outside%20the%20writer%2Fdirector%E2%80%99s%20house%20for%20%3Cem%3EOppenheimer%3C%2Fem%3E.%20This%20has%20resulted%20in%20Nolan%E2%80%99s%20most%20unambiguously%20personal%20film%20in%20a%20long%20time%2C%20where%20he%20takes%20the%20life%20of%20a%20scientist%20%E2%80%93%20treated%20like%20a%20prophet%20during%20a%20World%20War%2C%20and%20later%20demoted%20to%20a%20mortal%20as%20soon%20as%20he%20began%20casting%20doubts%20on%20his%20own%20breakthrough.%20Gary%20Oldman%20as%20president%20Harry%20Truman%20%E2%80%93%20is%20outstanding%20in%20the%20one%20scene%2C%20becoming%20the%20face%20of%20an%20establishment%20that%20winces%20at%20Oppenheimer%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Ccry-baby%E2%80%9D%20attitude%2C%20when%20he%20asks%20them%20to%20scale%20down%20on%20nuclear%20weapons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20stirring%20things%20about%20this%20excellently%20dense%20and%20jumpy%20biopic%20is%20that%20Nolan%20never%20tries%20to%20reconcile%20his%20subjects%E2%80%99%20contradictions.%20If%20anything%2C%20he%20realises%20the%20futility%20of%20trying%20to%20know%20the%20unknowable.%20%3Cem%3EWho%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20J.%20Robert%20Oppenheimer%3F%20A%20film%20can%20make%20an%20educated%20guess%20based%20on%20recorded%20actions%20and%20anecdotes.%20There%20will%20always%20be%20gaps%2C%20and%20Nolan%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20pretend%20otherwise.%20Instead%2C%20choosing%20to%20grapple%20with%20a%20larger%20question%20%E2%80%93%20what%20does%20Oppenheimer%E2%80%99s%20predicament%20mean%20for%20the%20generation%20today%3F%20Only%20our%20lives%20depend%20on%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689956828000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F21215129%2FUntitled-design-2023-07-21T215101.001.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fthe-many-sides-and-dilemmas-of-oppenheimer-father-of-the-atomic-bomb%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Director%20Christopher%20Nolan's%20thoughtful%20film%20is%20full%20of%20familiar%20stars%2C%20but%20it%20is%20Cillian%20Murphy%20as%20the%20protagonist%20who%20gives%20it%20depth.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fthe-many-sides-and-dilemmas-of-oppenheimer-father-of-the-atomic-bomb%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Some%20will%20go%20hungry%2C%20some%20will%20starve'%3A%20Global%20rice%20shortages%20feared%20after%20India%20bans%20exports%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689955500000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F07%2F70x70%2Fskynews-neville-lazarus-haryana_6225936.jpg%3F20230721144241%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fsome-will-go-hungry-some-will-starve-global-rice-shortages-feared-after-india-bans-exports-12925097%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Indian%C2%A0government%20has%20banned%20the%20export%20of%20non-basmati%C2%A0white%20rice%20-%C2%A0trigging%20fears%20of%20shortages%20and%20price%20rises%20across%20the%20world.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A248%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fsome-will-go-hungry-some-will-starve-global-rice-shortages-feared-after-india-bans-exports-12925097%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fam