s%20of%20the%20dead%20are%20passed%20to%20their%20son).%20We%20survived%20on%20%3Cem%3Enamak%20mirch%20roti%20%3C%2Fem%3E(flatbread%20with%20chilly%20and%20salt)%20for%20days%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20recalls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fshashi-cooking-classes-3-1689859353.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Shashi%E2%80%99s%20sons%20were%20aged%20five%20and%20seven%20years%20when%20her%20husband%20died.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fshashi-cooking-classes-3-1689859353.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fshashi-cooking-classes-3-1689859353-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fshashi-cooking-classes-3-1689859353-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fshashi-cooking-classes-3-1689859353-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fshashi-cooking-classes-3-1689859353-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-324600%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EShashi%E2%80%99s%20sons%20were%20aged%20five%20and%20seven%20years%20when%20her%20husband%20died.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNeither%20did%20my%20%3Cem%3Epeehar%20%3C%2Fem%3E(father%E2%80%99s%20home)%20nor%20my%20in-laws%20support%20me%20in%20raising%20my%20children.%20So%2C%20after%20my%20husband%E2%80%99s%20death%2C%20I%20had%20to%20withdraw%20them%20from%20their%20English%20medium%20school%20and%20enrol%20them%20in%20a%20government-run%20school%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20make%20ends%20meet%2C%20Shashi%20washed%20tourists%E2%80%99%20clothes%20until%202008%20when%20she%20had%20a%20visitor%20from%20Ireland.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHe%20told%20us%20that%20he%20admires%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F311742%2Fgujarat-woman-chef-fought-stereotypes-to-start-secret-kitchen-restaurant-australia-aanal-kotak%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIndian%20food%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20lot.%20And%20since%20he%20was%20our%20guest%2C%20I%20thought%20of%20offering%20him%20the%20food%20we%20had.%20I%20did%20not%20have%20sufficient%20means%2C%20so%20I%20could%20only%20serve%20him%20%3Cem%3Eroti%20sabzi%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Ebut%20he%20said%20it%20was%20delicious.%20He%20was%20in%20Udaipur%20for%20four%20to%20five%20days%20and%20he%20visited%20us%20each%20day.%20I%20would%20cook%20various%20vegetables%20for%20him%20and%20he%20relished%20them%20all.%20He%20even%20wanted%20to%20learn%20how%20the%20food%20was%20cooked%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20incident%20gave%20her%20the%20idea%20to%20start%20cooking%20classes%20for%20tourists%20and%20%E2%80%98Shashi%20Cooking%20Classes%E2%80%99%20was%20born.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EHer%20%E2%80%98English%20Vinglish%E2%80%99%20Moment%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecalling%20her%20initial%20experience%20of%20setting%20up%20the%20class%2C%20she%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20did%20not%20have%20a%20good%20kitchen.%20We%20just%20had%20a%20small%20wooden%20table.%20Our%20first%20guest%20was%20an%20Australian%20couple.%20I%20was%20so%20nervous%2C%20my%20hands%20were%20shaking%20and%20I%20was%20also%20sweating.%20I%20even%20dropped%20a%20teacup%2C%20but%20they%20encouraged%20me%20by%20saying%20that%20it%20was%20okay%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fshashi-cooking-classes-1-1689859194.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Shashi%20runs%20cooking%20classes%20to%20teach%20Indian%20cuisine%20to%20foreign%20tourists.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fshashi-cooking-classes-1-1689859194.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fshashi-cooking-classes-1-1689859194-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fshashi-cooking-classes-1-1689859194-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fshashi-cooking-classes-1-1689859194-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fshashi-cooking-classes-1-1689859194-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-324596%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EShashi%20runs%20cooking%20classes%20to%20teach%20Indian%20cuisine%20to%20foreign%20tourists.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20my%20next%20class%2C%20there%20were%20French%20tourists.%20They%20did%20not%20know%20English%20and%20I%20did%20not%20know%20French.%20They%20would%20look%20at%20my%20face%2C%20I%20would%20look%20at%20theirs!%20If%20they%20said%20%3Cem%3Edekho%3C%2Fem%3E%20(%3Cem%3Ed%E2%80%99accord%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20French%20means%20%E2%80%98okay%E2%80%99%20and%20%3Cem%3Edekho%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20Hindi%20means%20%E2%80%98see%E2%80%99)%2C%20I%20would%20start%20staring%20at%20places%20and%20everyone%20would%20burst%20into%20laughter%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20shares%20amidst%20giggles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20language%20barriers%2C%20Shashi%20received%20much%20affection%20from%20foreign%20guests%20who%20also%20tried%20to%20teach%20her%20their%20languages.%20From%20knowing%20only%20Rajasthani%2C%20she%20can%20now%20speak%20basic%20words%20in%20English%20and%20several%20other%20foreign%20languages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20had%20to%20learn%20these%20languages%20because%2C%20without%20that%2C%20it%20would%20be%20difficult%20to%20explain%20my%20cooking%20methods%20to%20foreigners.%20For%20example%2C%20I%20learnt%20that%20%3Cem%3Eaata%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20known%20as%20whole%20wheat%20flour%20in%20English%20and%20%3Cem%3Efarine%20de%20bl%C3%A9%20entier%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20French%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says%2C%20while%20carefully%20pronouncing%20the%20words.%20To%20memorise%20them%2C%20she%20would%20write%20all%20these%20words%20in%20Hindi%20in%20her%20diary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EA%20Recipe%20to%20Success%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20admirers%20of%20Indian%20cuisine%20reach%20Shashi%20Cooking%20Classes%20through%20local%20guides%2C%20tour%20operators%2C%20and%20bloggers.%20Shashi%20first%20teaches%20them%20how%20to%20prepare%20%3Cem%3Emasala%20chai%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20then%20moves%20on%20to%20%3Cem%3Echutneys%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20coriander%20and%20dried%20mango%2C%20followed%20by%20%3Cem%3Epakoras%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20paneer%2C%20potatoes%2C%20and%20mixed%20vegetables.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fshashi-cooking-classes-4-1689859582.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Shashi%20has%20trained%20at%20least%201%2C000%20foreigners%20from%20Italy%2C%20Russia%2C%20Ireland%2C%20Switzerland%2C%20and%20Poland%2C%20so%20far.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fshashi-cooking-classes-4-1689859582.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fshashi-cooking-classes-4-1689859582-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fshashi-cooking-classes-4-1689859582-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fshashi-cooking-classes-4-1689859582-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fshashi-cooking-classes-4-1689859582-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-324609%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EShashi%20has%20trained%20at%20least%201%2C000%20foreigners%20from%20Italy%2C%20Russia%2C%20Ireland%2C%20Switzerland%2C%20and%20Poland%2C%20so%20far.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20teaches%20them%20how%20to%20cook%20%3Cem%3Edal%20%3C%2Fem%3E(lentil%20gravy)%2C%20%3Cem%3Ealu%20gobi%20%3C%2Fem%3E(potato%20cauliflower%20stir%20fry)%2C%20paneer%20butter%20%3Cem%3Emasala%20%3C%2Fem%3E(gravy%20cooked%20with%20cottage%20cheese)%2C%20%3Cem%3Echapati%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3Egatte%20ki%20sabji%20%3C%2Fem%3E(a%20traditional%20Rajasthani%20curry%20made%20with%20chickpea%20flour%20sausages)%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3Enaan%3C%2Fem%3E%20(flatbread).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShashi%20cooks%20a%20unique%20kind%20of%20garlic%20cheese%20made%20from%20hung%20curd%2C%20pepper%2C%20and%20chopped%20garlic%20which%20is%20applied%20over%20hot%20%3Cem%3Enaan%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20%3Cem%3Echapati%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20served%20with%20tomato%20curry.%20%E2%80%9COur%20guests%20love%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says%20with%20pride.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20five-hour%20class%2C%20which%20is%20priced%20at%20INR%201%2C500%20per%20person%2C%20the%20guests%20relish%20the%20cooked%20meals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDaniel%20shares%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20learning%20experience%20is%20great%20mainly%20because%20the%20classes%20are%20organised%20at%20Shashi%E2%80%99s%20home.%20She%20tells%20you%20her%20life%20story%20also%20which%20helps%20us%20engage%20with%20her.%20Both%2C%20Shashi%20and%20her%20son%2C%20who%20helps%20her%20in%20cooking%2C%20are%20very%20didactic%3B%20not%20only%20in%20following%20recipes%2C%20but%20also%20in%20teaching%20the%20basics%20of%20Indian%20cuisine.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20love%20cooking%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20excited%20to%20use%20everything%20I%20learned%20from%20Shashi%E2%80%99s%20class%20in%20Spain.%20I%E2%80%99ll%20definitely%20put%20those%20skills%20into%20practice%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20840px)%20100vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fshashi-cooking-classes-2-1689859229.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22After%20a%20five-hour%20class%2C%20the%20guests%20relish%20the%20cooked%20meals.%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fshashi-cooking-classes-2-1689859229.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fshashi-cooking-classes-2-1689859229-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fshashi-cooking-classes-2-1689859229-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fshashi-cooking-classes-2-1689859229-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fshashi-cooking-classes-2-1689859229-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-324597%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22439%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EAfter%20a%20five-hour%20class%2C%20the%20guests%20relish%20the%20cooked%20meals.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShashi%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CMy%20focus%20is%20not%20to%20only%20earn%20an%20income%20from%20these%20guests%20but%20also%20to%20treat%20them%20nicely%20because%20they%20are%20our%20guests.%20They%20should%20be%20happy%20when%20they%20go%20back%20to%20their%20homes.%20Sometimes%2C%20they%20even%20pay%20me%20extra%20on%20their%20own%20out%20of%20love.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20than%20delectable%20meals%2C%20these%20tourists%20also%20enjoy%20Shashi%E2%80%99s%20company%2C%20who%20does%20not%20miss%20a%20chance%20to%20entertain%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20apply%20henna%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Eon%20their%20palms%20and%20help%20our%20women%20guests%20wear%20a%20saree%20with%20bangles%20and%20bindi.%20I%20also%20apply%20%3Cem%3Esindoor%20%3C%2Fem%3E(vermillion)%20to%20them.%20They%20are%20enthusiastic%20to%20participate%20in%20all%20these%20activities%20and%20show%20a%20keen%20interest%20in%20knowing%20the%20Indian%20culture.%20They%20often%20request%20me%20to%20narrate%20stories%20of%20gods%20and%20goddesses%2C%20explain%20the%20significance%20of%20%3Cem%3Etulsi%20%3C%2Fem%3E(basil)%20plant%2C%20etc%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20also%20celebrate%20their%20birthdays.%20In%20their%20own%20dialects%2C%20they%20lovingly%20call%20me%20%E2%80%98aunty%E2%80%99%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds%20with%20a%20smile.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Shashi%2C%20teaching%20these%20foreign%20tourists%20helps%20her%20feel%20empowered.%20%E2%80%9CI%20always%20believed%20in%20hard%20work.%20No%20one%20can%20defeat%20you%20if%20you%20believe%20in%20yourself.%20%3Cem%3ERoya%20daan%20nai%20milta%2C%20aur%20maangi%20bheek%20%3C%2Fem%3E(You%20won%E2%80%99t%20always%20get%20alms%20by%20crying).%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3EI%20have%20learnt%20that%20there%20is%20no%20point%20in%20crying%20in%20front%20of%20others%2C%20empower%20yourself%20to%20go%20on%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Pranita%20Bhat%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689946319000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fshashi-cooking-classes-3-1689859353.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D324582%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22After%20losing%20her%20husband%2C%20Shashikala%20Sanadhya%20took%20care%20of%20her%20family%20by%20starting%20Shashi%20Cooking%20Classes.%20So%20far%2C%20she%20has%20taught%